# patches/gsd-execute-phase-bypassperms.patch
# Phase 40 Plan 02 (D-126): auto-pass bypassPermissions to gsd-executor Task()
# calls so subagents inherit the parent's permission grants under CC 2.1.x.
# Re-applied at session-start by hooks/gsd-auto-reapply-patches.sh
# (wizard copies patches/ -> ~/.claude/gsd-local-patches/ on install).
#
# Root cause: Claude Code 2.1.x silently denies Bash tool calls inside
# subagents spawned without permission_mode="bypassPermissions".
# Phase 39 Wave 2 retro item — promoted to Phase 40 Plan 02.
#
# Schema note: Anthropic Agent SDK (CC 2.1.x) accepts permission_mode
# as a Task() keyword argument. If a future GSD upstream version already
# adds this arg, the dry-run step in applyShippedPatches() will detect
# "Reversed (or previously applied)" and skip silently (idempotent).
--- a/workflows/execute-phase.md
+++ b/workflows/execute-phase.md
@@ -419,10 +419,11 @@

    ```
    Task(
      subagent_type="gsd-executor",
      description="Execute plan {plan_number} of phase {phase_number}",
      model="{executor_model}",
+     permission_mode="bypassPermissions",
      isolation="worktree",
      prompt="
        <objective>
        Execute plan {plan_number} of phase {phase_number}-{phase_name}.
